parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The car locks and unlocks randomly
the remote start does not work sometimes
the battery loses connection
the radio/computer takes several minutes to boot up
the back-up camera lines do not show up
the radio continues playing after the car is turned off
the turn signal indicators do not make a sound
the seat belt
door ajar
and key in ignition warnings do not sound
and the collision notification and lane recognition do not produce an audible warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The radio/computer takes several minutes to boot up
the back-up camera lines do not show up
the radio continues playing after the car is turned off
the Bluetooth connection often disconnects
and the steering wheel controls do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses motive power and stalls without warning
requiring several attempts to restart the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag indicator light illuminates randomly
indicating a potential problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The tire is defective and needs to be replaced
which can cause a loss of control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.
symptoms: Airbag warning light turns on and off
airbags do not deploy in a crash
airbag indicator shows "off" even with a passenger in the seat
intermittent airbag malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake failure results in a car accident
inability to stop the vehicle in time.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sharp Chrome Peeling from Interior Door Handles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling of chrome from interior door handles can cause cuts and injuries to drivers and passengers, especially when they are away from home or not near medical supplies.
symptoms: Razor-sharp chrome peeling from interior door handles
cuts and lacerations on fingers and hands.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random shutdown of the engine can cause accidents, especially when it occurs at stop lights or stop signs, and can leave drivers stranded.
symptoms: Engine shuts off randomly
especially when idling at stop lights or stop signs
and may not turn back on for a few seconds to minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Shutdown with Check Engine Light
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine shutdown with the check engine light can cause accidents, especially when it occurs while driving, and can leave drivers stranded.
symptoms: Engine shuts off while driving
check engine light comes on
especially after rain
and may not turn back on until the gas tank is heated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting of the dashboard panel can cause a sticky or tacky feel, which can be distracting and uncomfortable for drivers, and may potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Upper dash panel has a sticky or tacky feel
especially in warm and sunny weather
and may sparkle at night due to melted spots.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent passenger seat airbag sensor can cause inconsistent airbag activation, which can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Passenger seat airbag sensor intermittently turns on for an adult sitting in the seat
even when the occupant meets the weight requirement
and may not consistently activate even with additional weight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system problems can cause hesitation, stalling, and jerking, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates to start
sputters
idles high
jerks
and has trouble accelerating
especially when the gas tank is below half full.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine performance issues can cause stalling, overheating, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls
overheats
shakes
and loses power
often accompanied by the illumination of the check engine warning indicator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbocharger problems can cause loss of power, stalling, and engine damage, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Bent turbo fins
engine stalling
and loss of power.
